title._content: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo San Diego California

description._content: Catalog #: 09_01648 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo San Diego California Additional Information: Harry Haw (on left) with Earl P. Andrew and an unidentified aircraft leaving to fly to a Conference in Chino, California. Handwritten inscription ""Hurt my back when I lifted the tail of the plane and tried to roll it back against the fence. 8:00 Left San Diego. 9:15 Arrived at Chino, landed at south airport. 2:30 Left Chino. 3:30 Arrived at Long Beach. Gassed up. 4:00 Left Long Beach. 5:00 Arrived at Lindbergh Field, San Diego"", Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
